What you can do

Use the software freely for research, education, personal analysis, or non-commercial projects.

Modify, improve, fork, or adapt the code.

Publish your own improved open-source versions — as long as they remain fully open.

What you cannot do

No monetization of any kind — no sales, consulting, subscriptions, paywalls, tokens, crypto, bartering, or paid services based on this software.

No closed-source derivatives — all forks and adaptations must remain open-source and publicly accessible.

No proprietary usage in commercial or revenue-generating products.
